{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3111212,"name":"Oliver","username":"ohowe","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/ohowe/{size}/221361_2.png","created_at":"2022-12-16T01:21:21.693Z","cooked":"

We are happy to report that we had the opportunity to build three robots this offseason!

The first of these was a kitbot chassis with a shovel type thing on the front for the groundbreaking of our new science and innovation center being built on campus.

Pictures

The team with digbot1600×1067 299 KB

Digbot lifting a CAT1600×1067 324 KB

  • GitHub Link

The second bot was an swerve chassis using SDS’s mk4i. The code is still being actively developed.

  • Onshape Link
  • GitHub Link

The third was a WCD chassis with a spinning table on top of it used at our family potluck to serve deserts to parents.

We’d be happy to answer any questions you might have.
